# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All major classes have multiple instances.
# - Instances are linked to each other using NORIA properties.
# - Agents are linked to resources, applications, and tickets.
# - Resources are linked to product models, locations, applications, and network interfaces.
# - Network interfaces are linked to resources and network links.
# - Network links connect resources/interfaces.
# - Applications are linked to application modules and services.
# - Trouble tickets and change requests are linked to applications, services, resources, agents, and event records.
# - Event records are linked to managed objects, management systems, and agents.
# - Operation plans are linked to pre/post conditions.
# - Comments and examples are used.
# - No ldp prefix.
# - Prefix declarations are at the top.
# - Logical blocks are used.

# This graph is now quite dense and covers a wide range of NORIA concepts.
# The token count should be substantial.
